Bash("c:\\Repos\\MFViewer\\venv\\Scripts\\python.exe" -c "
import json
import numpy as np
from pathlib import Path
import sys
sys.path.insert\(0, ''.''\)

from mfviewer.data.engine_model import EngineConfig, AlphaNModel, SCIPY_AVAILABLE
from mfviewer.data.ve_map_manager import VEMapManager, find_bin_index
from mfviewer.data.parser import MFLogParser

print\(f''SCIPY_AVAILABLE: {SCIPY_AVAILABLE}''\)

# Load config
config_file = r''C:\\Users\\gf006\\AppData\\Local\\MFViewer\\MFViewer\\engine_configs.json''
with open\(config_file, ''r''\) as f:
    data = json.load\(f\)
config_dict = list\(data.values\(\)\)[0]
config = EngineConfig.from_dict\(config_dict\)

# Load map
map_file = r''C:\\Repos\\MFViewer\\mfviewer\\data\\base_fuel_ve_map.csv''
result = VEMapManager.load_map\(Path\(map_file\)\)
base_ve_map, rpm_axis, load_axis, load_type = result

# Load log
log_file = r''C:\\Users\\gf006\\Documents\\Haltech\\Nexus Maps and Data Logs\\RCR 599 Prototipo\\Logs\\2025-12-31_0226pm_Log465.csv''
parser = MFLogParser\(log_file, use_cache=True\)
telemetry = parser.parse\(\)

# Get channels
rpm_data = telemetry.get_channel_data\(''RPM''\).values.copy\(\)
tps_data = telemetry.get_channel_data\(''Throttle Position''\).values.copy\(\)
lambda_data = telemetry.get_channel_data\(''Wideband O2 Overall''\).values.copy\(\)

# Convert lambda
valid_mask = \(lambda_data > 0\) & \(lambda_data < 3000\)
lambda_data[~valid_mask] = np.nan
lambda_data = lambda_data / 1000.0

# Bin data
rows, cols = len\(load_axis\), len\(rpm_axis\)
hit_count_map = np.zeros\(\(rows, cols\), dtype=np.int32\)
lambda_sum_map = np.zeros\(\(rows, cols\), dtype=np.float64\)

for i in range\(len\(rpm_data\)\):
    rpm = rpm_data[i]
    tps = tps_data[i]
    lambda_val = lambda_data[i]
    if np.isnan\(rpm\) or np.isnan\(tps\) or np.isnan\(lambda_val\):
        continue
    if lambda_val < 0.5 or lambda_val > 1.5 or rpm < 500:
        continue
    col = find_bin_index\(rpm, rpm_axis\)
    row = find_bin_index\(tps, load_axis\)
    if row is not None and col is not None:
        hit_count_map[row, col] += 1
        lambda_sum_map[row, col] += lambda_val

# Compare min_samples = 5 vs min_samples = 10 \(default in UI\)
for min_samples in [5, 10, 20]:
    measured_mask = hit_count_map >= min_samples
    
    rpm_arr, tps_arr, ve_arr, weights = [], [], [], []
    for row in range\(rows\):
        for col in range\(cols\):
            if measured_mask[row, col]:
                avg_lambda = lambda_sum_map[row, col] / hit_count_map[row, col]
                correction = avg_lambda / 1.0
                corrected_ve = base_ve_map[row, col] * correction
                rpm_arr.append\(rpm_axis[col]\)
                tps_arr.append\(load_axis[row]\)
                ve_arr.append\(corrected_ve\)
                weights.append\(hit_count_map[row, col]\)
    
    rpm_arr = np.array\(rpm_arr, dtype=np.float64\)
    tps_arr = np.array\(tps_arr, dtype=np.float64\)
    ve_arr = np.array\(ve_arr, dtype=np.float64\)
    weights = np.array\(weights, dtype=np.float64\)
    
    print\(f''\\nmin_samples={min_samples}: {len\(rpm_arr\)} cells''\)
    
    if len\(rpm_arr\) >= 5:
        model = AlphaNModel\(config\)
        stats = model.fit\(rpm_arr, tps_arr, ve_arr, weights\)
        print\(f''  R²: {stats.r_squared:.3f}, RMSE: {stats.rmse:.2f}%''\)
        if model.fitted_params:
            print\(f''  Params: ve_base={model.fitted_params[""ve_base""]:.1f}, rpm_min={model.fitted_params[""rpm_min_factor""]:.3f}, tps_idle={model.fitted_params[""tps_idle_flow""]:.3f}, tps_exp={model.fitted_params[""tps_exponent""]:.2f}''\)
")
